narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about algebraic number theory - mainly the study of finite extensions of Q and their rings of integers.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: This is a good course to take if you're interested in algebra or number theory. Make sure you're well prepared with a strong background of algebra, advanced linear algebra, and Galois theory. Goncharov moves very fast, so it will be a struggle to keep up with his lectures.
